                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18470301-name-337" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18470301-name-337" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470301-name-337" type="surname" value="ASHCROFT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470301-name-337" type="given" value="PETER"></interp>PETER ASHCROFT</persName>
                  </hi>. On the 21th of the Feb., about half-past seven o'clock in the evening, I was walking in Aldgate—I perceived a hand in my pocket—turned round and missed my handkerchief—I saw the prisoner running—I</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184703010038"></xptr>
               <p>ran and caught him—my handkerchief laid along side of him, on the ground—I picked it up—this is it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">prisoner.</hi> You laid hold of two of us, and asked which it was that did it; some said him, and some said me; you had the other one first, and then you took me and kept me. <hi rend="italic">Witness.</hi> The prisoner came in contact with a boy who came out of a shop, without a hat—I only ran after the prisoner—they both fell down together, but I could not be mistaken in him—it was the prisoner I followed.</p>
               <p>
